roup, but instead may be controlled in part by resource trade-offs. High diversity in nutrient strategies between related species cautions again the use of simple functional groupings to draw conclusions about nutrient acquisition in tropical trees. {\textcopyright} 2018 The Authors. Journal of Ecology {\textcopyright} 2018 British Ecological Society},
