investigate the interactive influence of elevated temperature (3 degrees
C), wetting and drying (6-9\% increase and 5-6\% decrease of soil
moisture, respectively) on saprotrophic basidiomycete-mediated beech
(Fagus sylvatica) wood decomposition, as well as on hydrolytic
(beta-glucosidase, cellobiohydrolase, beta-xylosidase,
N-acetyl-glucosaminidase, acid phosphatase and leucine aminopeptidase)
