ptake and in AMF (scavenging strategy), whereas late-successional plant species invest in other chemoheterotrophic microorganisms in the rhizosphere (mining strategy) for nutrient acquisition. {\textcopyright} 2019 by The University of Chicago. All rights reserved.},
